3 (3) (I) “SENSITIVE INFORMATION” MEANS AN INDIVIDUAL’S:
4 1. SOCIAL SECURITY CARD OR SOCIAL SECURITY
5 NUMBER;
6 2. INDIVIDUAL TAXPAYER IDENTIFICATION NUMBER;
7 3. BIRTH CERTIFICATE;
8 4. RACIAL OR ETHNIC ORIGIN;
9 5. NATIONAL ORIGIN;
10 6. CITIZENSHIP OR IMMIGRATION STATUS; OR
11 7. RELIGIOUS OR PHILOSOPHICAL BELIEFS.
12 (II) “SENSITIVE INFORMATION” DOES NOT INCLUDE AN
13 INDIVIDUAL’S GOVERNMENT–ISSUED PHOTO IDENTIFICATION, SUCH AS A DRIVER’S
14 LICENSE.
15 (B) A COOPERATIVE HOUSING CORPORATION MAY NOT REQUIRE A MEMBER
16 OR UNIT OCCUPANT, OR THE GUEST OR CHILD OF A MEMBER OR UNIT OCCUPANT,
17 TO PROVIDE SENSITIVE INFORMATION AS A CONDITION FOR ACCESSING OR USING A
18 RECREATIONAL COMMON AREA, SUCH AS A READING LOUNGE, GAME ROOM,
19 PLAYGROUND, OR SWIMMING POOL.
